 with the 25th Infantry Division; andWhereas, In Vietnam, Sgt. Sherman served two tours, with the first being with the 101st Airborne Division and the second as a MACV Advisor with the South Vietnamese Army; andWhereas, Sgt. Sherman was awarded a Bronze Star Medal with one Oak Leaf Cluster, a Purple Heart, the Korean Service Medal with two service stars, United Nations Service Medal, Combat Infantryman Badge (2nd Award), National Defense Service Medal with two bronze service stars, the Republic of Vietnam Campaign Medal with 1960 device, the Air Medal, the Army Commendation Medal with two Oak Leaf Clusters, Six Overseas Service Bars, the Vietnam Cross of Gallantry with a Bronze Star, the Republic of Vietnam Armed Forces Honor Medal (2nd Class), and the Master Parachutist Badge; andWhereas, Sgt. Sherman went on to become a "Black Hat' Airborne instructor at Ft. Benning, GA until his retirement in 1974; andWhereas, Sgt. Sherman went on to become a self-employed carpenter and work for Smith Kline Pharmaceutical Company; andWhereas, Sgt. Sherman enjoyed fishing and will be remembered as a loving husband, father, grandfather, and friend to many people; therefore, be it Resolved by the Legislature of West Virginia:That the Division of Highways name Bridge Number: 16-055/00-011.96  () (16A134), (39.07833, -78.95205) locally known as MOOREFIELD INTERCHANGE, carrying WV 055 over US 48 (X) (Corridor H) in Hardy County the "Sgt. Ray “Mutt” Sherman Memorial Bridge," and, be it Further Resolved, That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to have made and be placed signs identifying the bridge as the "Sgt. Ray “Mutt” Sherman Memorial Bridge"; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk of the House forward a copy of this resolution to the Commissioner of the Division of Highways. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West V